# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# DIAMOND EMPIRE — Environment Configuration
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your Firebase configuration values.
# These values come from your Firebase project settings.
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit .env to version control!
# The .gitignore file should already exclude .env files.
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Firebase Configuration
# Get these values from: Firebase Console > Project Settings > General > Your apps
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_project_id.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_project_id.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_sender_id
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id

# Optional: Firebase Analytics
# VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com
# 2. Create a new project (or use existing)
# 3. Enable Authentication:
#    - Click "Authentication" in sidebar
#    - Click "Get started"
#    - Enable "Email/Password" provider
# 4. Enable Storage (optional, for profile photos):
#    - Click "Storage" in sidebar
#    - Click "Get started"
#    - Set up security rules
# 5. Get your config:
#    - Click gear icon > Project settings
#    - Scroll to "Your apps"
#    - Click the web icon (</>)
#    - Register app and copy config values
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

